# Week 4 Summary: LLM Benchmarking Assignment

## Goals
- Benchmark one or more LLMs on the **exact same prediction task** as Week 3's ML model
- Learn how to interact and manipulate an LLM directly

## Core Requirement
- Use the **same target definition** and the **same hold out test split** from Week 3
- Use a small subset of data

---

## What We're Looking For
- Reproducible notebook run in JupyterHub
- No R this time
  - Reference: https://www.dataquest.io/blog/jupyter-notebook-tutorial/
- Clean prompt design and outputs
- Reliable parsing to structured predictions
- Metrics computed comparably to Week 3
- Clear ML vs LLM comparison and concrete error analysis

---

## Deliverables

### 1. LLM Benchmarking Notebook (`llm_benchmark.ipynb`)
- Loads in your Week 3 target and test set
- Queries at least one LLM
- Converts the LLM response into a structured prediction
- Evaluates on Week 3 test set with same metrics

### 2. Prompt Set
- Final prompt template text
- Few-shot examples (if used)
- Reference: https://huggingface.co/docs/transformers/en/tasks/prompting

### 3. `README.md`
- Approach (your prompting and validation strategy)
- Error analysis (2-3 sentences and include failure examples)
- Repeatability steps

### 4. Results CSVs (per LLM tested)
- Include prompt, raw outputs, parsed predictions

